# Home Automation Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and update with your values

# Domain configuration
DOMAIN=example.com

# Timezone (e.g., America/New_York, Europe/London)
TZ=America/New_York

# Service Access URLs:
# Home Assistant: http://your-server-ip:8123
# Node-RED:       https://nodered.example.com
# MQTT Broker:    mqtt://your-server-ip:1883
#
# Note: Home Assistant uses host networking for device discovery
# Access it directly via IP:8123, not through Traefik
#
# Hardware Access:
# - For Zigbee/Z-Wave: Uncomment device mappings in docker-compose.yml
# - For Bluetooth: May need --privileged flag (already set)
# - Check device paths with: ls -la /dev/tty*
#
# First Time Setup:
# 1. Access Home Assistant at http://your-server-ip:8123
# 2. Create your account
# 3. Add integrations for your smart home devices
# 4. Connect Node-RED to Home Assistant for advanced automations
